Origin of data and legal foundations Data on deaths are based on the reports of the Austrian registrar's offices, which since 1.November 2014 are transmitted continously by the Central Civil Status Register. Until 2008 statistics covered all deaths of Austrian residents occurring in Austria. Since reporting year 2009 data also include deaths of main residents dying abroad. Regional assignment of the results is according to the last place of residence of the deceased person. Legal basis is the Civil Status Law. Other Metadata: http://www.statistik.at/web_en/statistics/population/deaths/index.html .)
